The paper deals with the query complexity of problems, which is a fundamental concept in computational complexity theory. The paper discusses the deterministic and non-deterministic query complexity of problems and introduces a new quantity, $D_k(P)$, which lies between these two values. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
